                            <comment id="15270844" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 15:33:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to test this if you can provide a patch for CCITTFaxFilter. The change should support G3, G32D and G4, and also the encodedByteAlign option.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15270954" author="pslabycz" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 16:40:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You mean to test my solution using the Twelve Monkeys implementation? Unfortunately, the decoder class in that library is not public, so for my quick and dirty test I have just copied it with some minor tweaks to avoid copying too many classes. Then, I have used it for the K&amp;gt;1 path only as it was used in my PDF. I believe this is the G3 and G32D variant, depending on the value of tiffOptions. As for G4, it would not be a big deal, except that I do not see a flag for the byte align option in the Twelve Monkeys library. Not sure whether it is not supported there or whether this is just lack of knowledge on my side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Apart from that, I could probably do this. The license of Twelve Monkeys allows copying provided that the copyright notice remains in the copied file. (At least this is how I understand it, but I am not a lawyer) This is no problem for a testing patch. But I do not know whether you could use it if you decide to take the solution instead of the current decoder implementation (which originally comes from Sun ImageIO and was made freely available by Sun some years ago).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271003" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 17:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;It has an Apache license, so this isn&apos;t a problem.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suspect that the encodedByteAlign option isn&apos;t supported&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/haraldk/TwelveMonkeys/blob/master/imageio/imageio-tiff/src/main/java/com/twelvemonkeys/imageio/plugins/tiff/CCITTFaxDecoderStream.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/haraldk/TwelveMonkeys/blob/master/imageio/imageio-tiff/src/main/java/com/twelvemonkeys/imageio/plugins/tiff/CCITTFaxDecoderStream.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
one would have to implement it. See in rev 1581603 and 1581602 / &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1074&quot; title=&quot;TIFFFaxDecoder5 when using PDFImageWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1074&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1074&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another problem in that code is &quot;continue&quot; with label. I&apos;ve never seen that one before, ever. When was this added to java?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271045" author="pslabycz" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 17:36:06 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; It has an Apache license, so this isn&apos;t a problem.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cool, that saves me some sorrows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I suspect that the encodedByteAlign option isn&apos;t supported one would have to implement it. See in rev 1581603 and 1581602 / &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1074&quot; title=&quot;TIFFFaxDecoder5 when using PDFImageWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1074&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1074&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can try, seems to be quite straightforward at a first glance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another problem in that code is &quot;continue&quot; with label. I&apos;ve never seen that one before, ever. When was this added to java?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is there since ever. See e.g. some examples at &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/branch.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/branch.html&lt;/a&gt;. I hope you are just exaggerating with the word &quot;problem&quot;? I find the code much better and more readable than the current decoder class in PDFBox. To the least, it does not need to jump hence and forth in the input and reads it byte by byte instead. Not that I would really understand what is going on in detail in either of the implementations. For that, one would have to study the standard first. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271062" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 17:46:00 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It has an Apache license, so this isn&apos;t a problem.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It doesn&apos;t use an Apache license, but the 3-clause BSD license. Which is ok as well, see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved#category-a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.apache.org/legal/resolved#category-a&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271099" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 18:01:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I thought he was using a JDK7 or JDK8 concept. So no problem there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The encodedByteAlign option means that after reading all the bits of a line, you have to skip bits until reaching a byte boundary. Maybe this can be done in decodeRow().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271232" author="pslabycz" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 19:10:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see. I misunderstood your earlier comment then, sorry. I have double-checked this now, the class compiles fine with java compliance set to 1.5. It would compile with older versions, too, except for the few annotations it is using.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271452" author="pslabycz" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 21:22:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, here is the patch. I did not manage to make it work with the G3 1D example from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1708&quot; title=&quot;IndexOutOfBoundsException on convertToImage with an embedded Fax-Image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, so I left the K=0 path untouched in the end. I have successfully tested a G3 2D example, G4 byte-aligned and G4 w/o byte align. Hope your results will be good as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15271508" author="tilman" created="Wed, 4 May 2016 21:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks... rendering fails for:&lt;/p&gt;
